## Task

You will receive a tuple of source documents (visible as `<document>`
context messages above). Each document contains a single short token of the
form `XXXX000`. Read every document and emit the tokens in the `order`
field as a tuple of strings IN THE EXACT ORDER the documents were supplied.

## Rules

- The number of tokens in `order` must match the number of supplied documents.
- The order of tokens in `order` must match the supply order of the documents
  (first document first, last document last).
- Do not invent or reorder tokens. Copy each token verbatim.
